##### Git LFS
# Binary engine assets are stored via Git LFS so the bytes do not bloat
# the main git object database. Order matters — these entries must come
# AFTER any earlier `binary` declaration for the same extension, because
# git applies the last matching attribute. Patterns are case-sensitive
# on the filename portion; both casings of common extensions are
# enumerated for upstream tutorial drops that use upper-case names.

# Image / texture
*.png  filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
*.PNG  filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
*.jpg  filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
*.JPG  filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
*.jpeg filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
*.JPEG filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
